AttributeList.Text: This function block handles all the logic for the digital alarms.

This network handles simulating the output value for testing and commissioning uses.
If SimulationMode and GlobalSimulation = FALSE, then the InputValue and the SimulationBit are set or reset to the corresponding value.
If SimulationMode or GlobalSimulation = TRUE, then the InputValue is set by the SimulationBit to the corresponding value. The SimulationBit can be modified from the HMI.
If ConfigurationMode is FALSE then RESET the SimulationMode bit to FALSE
Digital Simulation

This network sets the DelayTime for the Digital Alarm, in case there must be a time delay before the alarm is triggered.
If ExternalAlarm = TRUE, then 0 is moved into the DelayTime Variable. If ExternalAlarm = FALSE, then the DelayTime is set from the HMI.
DelayTime is multiplied by 1000, before being moved into the DelayTimer.PT, which is the Preset Variable for the DelayTimer.
Alarm Delay Time

This network is used to enable or disable dock mode for this digital signal.
If DockModeEnable and GlobalDockMode = TRUE, then the DockModeEnabled = TRUE. Which enables the DockMode for this Alarm.
If DockModeEnable or GlobalDockMode = FALSE, then the DockModeEnabled = FALSE. Which disables DockMode for this Alarm.
Dock Mode

This network is used to enable or disable unoccupied mode for this digital signal.
If #GlobalWord.Unoccupied Mode = TRUE AND #ConfigAlarm.Bools.UnoccupiedMode = TRUE, then the UnoccupiedModeEnabled = TRUE. Which enables the UnoccupiedMode for this Alarm.
If #GlobalWord.Unoccupied Mode = FALSE OR #ConfigAlarm.Bools.UnoccupiedMode = FALSE, then the UnoccupiedModeEnabled = FALSE. Which disables the UnoccupiedMode for this Alarm.
Unoccupied Mode

This network contains the logic to Enable or Disable the alarm for this digital signal.
If #ConfigAlarm.Bools.AlarmDisable = TRUE OR (DockModeEnabled = TRUE AND #UnoccupiedModeEnabled = FALSE), then #AlarmDisabled = TRUE. Which DISABLES THE ALARM. It will NOT come on due to any circumstance.
If #ConfigAlarm.Bools.AlarmDisable = FALSE AND (DockModeEnabled = FALSE OR #UnoccupiedModeEnabled = TRUE) , then #AlarmDisabled = FALSE. Which ENABLES THE ALARM. It will come on when the InputValue goes to the alarm state.
Alarm Enabling And Disabling

This network monitors for the alarm condition.
The ContactType is set from the HMI, for if the alarm should be on 0 or 1.
If InputValue and ContactType are both TRUE or FALSE at the same time, and AlarmDisabled = FALSE, and the Alarm Qualifiers are TRUE, then the DelayTimer for the Alarm begins timing.
When the Output of the timer (DelayTimer.Q) finishes, the AlarmActive is set to TRUE.
Monitoring For Alarm Condition

This network sets the Alarm Output.
If the Alarm is active (AlarmActive = TRUE), The Alarm is latched (AlarmLatch = TRUE), or the Alarm is in Test mode (AlarmTest = TRUE) then Alarm is set to TRUE and the Alarm is sent to the HMI.
Alarm Active

This network handles acknowledging the alarm.
When AlarmAcknowledge = TRUE, the AlarmAcknowledgeONS (Oneshot) prevents the bit from being help on.
If AlarmLatch = TRUE and AlarmAcknowledge OR Acknowledge = TRUE then AlarmAcknowledged is set to TRUE. And the Alarm is Acknowledged. Which Silences the AlarmHorns and disables the flashing of the Alarm on the HMI.
If AlarmLatch = FALSE, then AlarmAcknowledged is set to FALSE.
If AlarmAcknowledged = TRUE and AlarmActive = FALSE, then AlarmLatch is set to FALSE, and the Alarm is unlatched.
Alarm Acknowledgement

This network handles the Alarm Horn.
If AlarmTest = TRUE, then the AlarmHornTest_Delay Timer begins timing. After 250ms the Output is triggerred. And prevents the Horn from Latching on during testing.
If Severity > 100, and Alarm = TRUE, and AlarmSilenced, Silence and AlarmHornTest_Delay.Q = FALSE, then the AlarmHorn = TRUE. And the AlarmHorn is enabled.
If AlarmTest = TRUE then the AlarmHorn = TRUE and the AlarmHorn is enabled.
If Severity > 200, Alarm = TRUE and AlarmAcknowledged = FALSE, then StationDisableBypass = TRUE.
If Alarm = TRUE and Silence, AlarmAcknowledged or Silence_MCR = TRUE, then AlarmSilenced is set to TRUE. Which Silences the AlarmHorn.
If the Severity is between 100 and 150, the AlarmHornReactivationDelayTimer.PT is set to 600s. If the Severity is between 150 and 200, the AlarmHornReactivationDelayTimer.PT is set to 120s. If the Severity is above 200, the AlarmHornReactivationDelayTimer.PT is set to 0s.
If Alarm = TRUE, AlarmSilenced = TRUE, and AlarmSilenced_MCR = FALSE, then the ReactivationDelay Timer begins timing.
If Alarm = FALSE, or the ReactivationDelayTimer Output = FALSE, then the AlarmSilenced is set to FALSE, so the alarm is unsilenced.
Alarm Horn

This network handles the Alarm Horn in the MCR.
If the Severity is greater then 100, and Alarm = TRUE, and AlarmSilenced_MCR and Silence_MCR = FALSE, then AlarmHorn_MCR = FALSE.
If Alarm = TRUE, and Silence_MCR or AlarmAcknowledged = TRUE, then AlarmSilenced_MCR is set to FALSE.
If Alarm = FALSE, then AlarmSilenced_MCR is reset to FALSE.
The AlarmHorn in the MCR does not have a reactivation delay, and cannot be silenced from outside the MCR. Once the alarm is silenced from the MCR, it is silenced permenantly until the alarm resets.
Alarm Horn MCR

This network sets the appropriate Annunciator group bit based on the #ConfigAlarm.Group Value AND #Alarm = TRUE 16#00 = #GlobalWord."Port Propulsion Annunciator" 16#01 = #GlobalWord."Stbd Propultion Annunciator" 16#02 = #GlobalWord."HPU Annunciator" 16#04 = #GlobalWord."Electrical Annunciator" 16#08 = #GlobalWord."Auxilliary/Domestic Annunciator" 16#10 = #GlobalWord."Fire Annunciator" 16#03 = #GlobalWord."Bilge Annunciator" 16#07 = #GlobalWord."CCAMS Annunciator" 16#0F = #GlobalWord."Fitness Annunciator" AND #GlobalWord."Fitness Alarm Column" 16#1F = #GlobalWord."Tank Annunciator"
Annunciator Group Output
This network sets the #GlobalWord.Horn = TRUE if #AlarmHorn is TRUE
Alarm Horn
This network sets the #GlobalWord.Horn MCR AND #GlobalWord."Machinery Alarm Column" = TRUE if #AlarmHorn_MCR is TRUE
Alarm Horn MCR
This network sets the #GlobalWord.StationDisableBypass = TRUE if the following conditions are met: - #ConfigAlarm.Severity >= 16#08; AND - #Alarm = TRUE; AND - #AlarmAcknowledged = FALSE.
Station Disable Bypass
This network sets the #GlobalWord.Loudhailer bit to TRUE if the following conditions are met: - #UnoccupiedModeEnabled = TRUE; AND - #Alarm = TRUE; AND - #AlarmAcknowledged = FALSE.
Unoccupied Mode Loudhailer

This network sets the #UnAck output to TRUE for connection to the AlarmCounting Arrays. if the following conditions are met: - #Alarm = TRUE; AND - #AlarmAcknowledged = FALSE.
ELSE #UnAck = FALSE.
Unacknowledged
This network moves the #ConfigAlarm.Severity to the #Severity output for connection to the AlarmCounting Arrays
Severity
This network is used to move the #AlarmSilenced and #AlarmSilenced_MCR to the outputs for visibility outside of the block.
Silenced
This network contains all the logic to write the existing alarm configuration values from the PLC memory to the HMI.
Configuration Mode - Write Existing Values to HMI
This network contains all the logic to read all the new alarm configuration values from the HMI to the PLC memory.
Configuration Mode - Read New Values from HMI
Digital Alarm Handler
